title: Golmaal 3
subTitle: Cupid strikes when Pritam, a single father, comes across his college sweetheart, Geeta, in Goa. However, when their respective children go at war with each other, the two find it difficult to reunite.

title: Benaam
subTitle: Amit and Sheela, a married couple, save a stabbing victim from an attempted murder. However, things take a dark turn when they start receiving death threats from an unknown person.

title: Lorie
subTitle: Geeta Malhotra suffers a miscarriage and yearns to have a child. One day, she finds a lost child and brings him up as her own, only to face trial for his abduction later.

title: Jai Vikraanta
subTitle: When a poor, honest farmer from rural India is killed by a greedy landlord, his son, Vikraanta, takes a vow to avenge his murder.

title: Deewana
subTitle: A newlywed Kajal gets widowed when her husband, Ravi, is killed by his enemies. She moves to another city and gets married to Raja but her life takes a turn when Ravi returns from the dead.

title: Singham Returns
subTitle: Bajirao Singham, an honest police officer, encounters Babaji, a god-man with connections to high profile politicians, when he investigates the death of an officer from his team.

title: Swarag Se Sunder
subTitle: Two brothers struggle to keep their family together as external forces like the younger brother's father-in-law try to break them apart.

title: Khuda Gawah
subTitle: Badshah Khan travels to India to behead the man who killed Benazir's father and win her hand in marriage. He succeeds in his mission but is caught by Ranveer Singh, a jailor.

title: Khullam Khulla Pyaar Karen
subTitle: Rival enemies Damani and Goverdhan arrange a marriage between their children, Vicky and Priti. But when Vicky goes missing, Raja poses as him and falls in love with Priti.

title: Khullam Khulla Pyaar Karen
subTitle: Rival enemies Damani and Goverdhan arrange a marriage between their children, Vicky and Priti. But when Vicky goes missing, Raja poses as him and falls in love with Priti.

title: Lakshmanrekha
subTitle: Amar sets out to avenge his father's death but gets beaten to the brink of death. He returns to carry on his vendetta, only to be confronted by Vicky, a criminal-turned-policeman and his close friend.

title: Dekh Tamasha Dekh
subTitle: The death of a religiously ambiguous man in a rural Indian town leads to tensions between two factions of the Hindu and Muslim communities over the body.

title: Dhanwaan
subTitle: Kashinath and Imli love each other. However, things take a turn when a wealthy woman, Anjali, meets Kashinath and falls in love with him, whereas Imli reveals that she suffers from a heart ailment.

title: Kahin Pyar Na Ho Jaye
subTitle: Prem's heart fills with despair when the woman he loves fails to show up for their wedding day. However, his life soon takes an unexpected turn with the arrival of a new neighbour.

title: Deewana Mastana
subTitle: Neha, a psychiatrist, faces a difficult situation when her patient and a thief fall in love with her and compete against each other to win her heart.

title: Dil Hai Tumhaara
subTitle: Sarita raises Shalu, her spouse's love child, and her daughter, Nimmi, but she does not forgive Shalu's past. When she discovers that Shalu is growing close to Nimmi's lover, things become worse.

title: Arjun
subTitle: Arjun has faced an uphill task, be it his education, career or even family life. When widespread corruption, crime and injustice take a toll on him, he decides to revolt but more betrayals await him.

title: Amar Akbar Anthony
subTitle: Three brothers, each raised in different religious households, reunite after many years in a chance encounter. They set out to take revenge on those responsible for separating them.

title: Amar Akbar Anthony
subTitle: Three brothers, each raised in different religious households, reunite after many years in a chance encounter. They set out to take revenge on those responsible for separating them.

title: Shriman Shrimati
subTitle: Appalled by the numerous problems faced by middle-class families, a wealthy couple decide to forsake their luxuries and live among the common people to make a difference in society.

title: Nachnewale Gaanewale
subTitle: Two friends sing and dance at functions for a living and decide to get their respective children married to each other. To their dismay, the son refuses to comply.

title: Jaal
subTitle: Fate plays a cruel game when Shankar gets hired by a rich woman named Amita who bears an uncanny resemblance with Meenabai, the person who breaks his family apart.

title: Andolan
subTitle: Adarsh and Aniket are two brothers who study in the same college. However, when they graduate and plan to establish a career, both of them choose different paths and gradually drift apart.

title: Yeshwant
subTitle: Yeshwant, an honest police inspector, is framed and arrested for a murder. However, after being released from prison, he learns that his wife is having an affair.

title: Gabbar Is Back
subTitle: The city's administration wrongs Aditya, a commoner. To avenge his tragedy, he disguises himself as a vigilante, Gabbar, and teams up with honest government officers to expose the corrupt.

title: Itihaas
subTitle: Naina, who is betrothed to an influential man, falls in love and elopes with Karan, the son of an employee of her fiance. Soon, bounty hunters start hunting the duo to claim a hefty reward.

title: Ajnabee
subTitle: Raj and Priya befriend their new neighbours Vicky and Sonia. One day, Raj wakes up in Vicky's house and finds out that Sonia is killed and he is framed for it.
